essible analysis of three crucial economic issues: the growth and composition of undergraduate enrollments, the supply of faculty in the academic labor market, and the cost of operating colleges and universities. The study provides valuable insights for administrators and scholars of education.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aBusiness. 0aCollege attendance. 0aCollege costs. 0aCollege teachers. 0aEducation, Higher. 0aEducation. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / General.2bisacsh1 aEhrenberg, Ronald G., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGetz, Malcolm, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226110622423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226110622.jpg  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles